    <!-- FAQ Answers -->
    <string name="faq_answer_add_meal">To add a meal, tap the \'+\' button on the dashboard. You can then search for food items, scan a barcode, or manually enter nutrition information.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_track_calories">Your calories are automatically tracked when you add meals. The dashboard shows your daily calorie intake and progress toward your goals.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_set_goals">Go to Settings and scroll down to \'Nutrition Goals\'. You can set daily targets for calories, protein, carbs, fat, fiber, and sodium.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_add_exercise">Tap the \'+\' button on the dashboard and select \'Add Exercise\'. You can choose from cardio, strength training, or bodyweight exercises.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_view_progress">Tap the analytics icon (bar chart) on the dashboard to view your weekly and monthly progress, including exercise history and nutrition trends.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_change_date">Use the calendar icon on the dashboard to select a different date, or use the arrow buttons to navigate day by day.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_scan_barcode">When adding a meal, tap the barcode scanner icon. Point your camera at the product\'s barcode to automatically find nutrition information.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_edit_entries">Tap on any meal or exercise entry in your daily log to view details. From there, you can edit or delete the entry.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_change_theme">Go to Settings and select your preferred theme: Light, Dark, or System Default.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_change_language">Go to Settings and select your preferred language from the Language option.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_tef_bonus" formatted="false">The TEF Bonus reflects the extra calories your body burns when digesting and processing food, especially proteins. Different macronutrients raise metabolism by varying amounts: fats about 0-5%, carbohydrates 5-15%, and protein 20-30%. Although you shouldn\'t rely heavily on this bonus for precise calorie budgeting, it\'s a helpful nudge towards eating more protein-rich meals, which can slightly boost your daily calorie burn and help with satiety. For a detailed scientific overview, you can check out this comprehensive review on the thermic effect of food.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_food_source">We use Open Food Facts, a collaborative database of food products from around the world. It\'s a free, open-source project that relies on contributions from users worldwide. The database includes nutritional information, ingredients, and even environmental impact scores. If you want to contribute to this open database, you can download their mobile app.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_exercise_source">The exercise database comes from an open-source repository maintained by Yuhonas. While NutCracker might incorporate its own translations in the future, this is not a priority at the moment. The exercises are currently only available in English, but the database is comprehensive and includes detailed instructions for various types of workouts.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_data_collected">NutCracker doesn\'t even have a server, so no individual data is collected. We don\'t know how many users we have nor what they are doing with this app. If your information is ever lost, we have no one to recover it. Refer to our Terms of Use on the settings screen for more info.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_make_money">We don\'t. Since the information comes from publicly available databases we have no servers so the only cost involved in this app is the hours of the developers, which is given for free as a hobby. There are also no trackers, no data brokerage, and no ads so even if 3 million people download it tomorrow, not a single penny will be made from this and we want to keep it like that.</string>
    <string name="faq_answer_logo_means">It is a close-up of a NutCracker belly and also a person doing a stretch. Did you notice it before?</string>
    
